deck: "The Awakened" redefines the way Graphic Novels are experienced, by merging real life people and classic graphic novel layouts and storytelling. The experience will leave you feeling as though you just experience your first still frame movie.
description:
The year is 2020; Corbin Reed is a 24 year old orphan male. In the year 2004 Scientist began experimenting on orphans for military grade human performance enhancers by taking bacteria found from the 1947 Roswell crash site in New Mexico and directly injecting it into the Motor cortex of the hosts brain allowing the bacteria to bond with the host, while giving the host enhanced physical agility and strength as well as rapid healing and enhanced senses. Thinking the project was a failure the project was scrapped and forgotten. 20 years later the orphanage was purchased by a huge upcoming research corporation known as Teslacorp. Teslacorp. is a leader in producing alternative energy sources. The scientists didn’t discover the “Awakened” because the children didn’t begin to show signs till they reached maturity, males between ages 23-25 years and females between ages 20- 22 years. At the peak of maturity the hybrids become fully “Awakened”. Each “Awakened individual has a unique elemental physical state and ability. Corbin, fire, Ashlyn, Water, Darren, Earth and so on.

During the demolition of the orphanage to make way for Teslacorp’s new headquarters, workers uncovered some old documents describing in detail the experiments that had taken place and gave it to Teslacorp C.E.O. Lee Stevens. At this point Teslacorp makes it a top priority to track down the alleged 12 “Awakened” and harvest their abilities as the ultimate alternative energy source, making trillions of dollars and becoming the new global energy supply allowing them to rule the world. The main characters have elemental abilities that are each unique. These hybrids are referred to and known as “The Awakened”. A female by the name of Ashlyn is looking for the “Awakened” as well. Ashlyn herself is an “Awakened”, and had been captured once as well as escaped capture from Teslacorp on numerous occasions. After Corbin handles The Teslacorp agents, Ashlyn helps him escape, and tells Corbin she knows about his abilities and explains what is going on as well as telling him she is searching for the other “Awakened” as well to warn them. Corbin denies having abilities because he didn’t know he had any but over the course of 2 weeks Ashlyn helps Corbin control his abilities. Frustrated to see some results with the new energy source, Lee Stevens becomes obsessed with the “Awakened”. Lee Stevens finds some remaining bacteria from the original experiments and recreates the experiment on himself; becoming an “Awakened” temporarily due to his application process and then believes he is unstoppable and sets out a new campaign to destroy the remaining “Awakened”. By completing this task no one would be able to stop him and he would be the ultimate “Awakened” with new endless energy source and the world would be his for the taking. During their journey through the series, Corbin and Ashlyn begin to fall for one another. Just as they once had feelings for each other when they were children at the orphanage. Darren and Corbin are at odds with each other due to their personal relationships with Ashlyn from the past. All the Awakened characters grew up for a short time together while at the orphanage.
name: The Awakened
